Text.Value: For all the gifts Bhaal's children inherit - a peaceful night's sleep is not among them.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* CINE_StepForward_to_StandL_01, adding grip for Scimitars. Match end pose to DWS_CINE_Draw_Idle_01. <CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Jaheira steps forward, and we see that she's holding her scimitars, blades bared.

Text.Value: Is this the reward for my confession? A dagger in the night?
What more could you need?
This power will save the world from the Absolute. The price doesn't matter.
Well, you cannot understand Boo's wisdom. So I suppose we must listen to Jaheira instead.
*You rest with the knowledge that you are being watched over. Or indeed, guarded.*
There is one last piece I've been toying with. A terrible and familiar power I've sensed around you for some time.
I think I can guess. Visions of blood on your hands. The blood in your veins, perhaps.
I don't think I have any -
Distracting you.
NO!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Jerking his head furiously, mind-meld dissipating

Text.Value: In another time - with another of your kind - we found a better way. I would dearly like to find it again.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* DWS_CINE_Stow_01 for Jaheira stowing her weapons.<CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Relaxing, Jaheira sighs and shethes her weapons. She steps back [to stand beside Minsc if he's present], giving the player room to stand.

Text.Value: It is not guidance I offer, but a leash. We will help you to control yourself - until you can free yourself of these urges, and use the Slayer form freely.

EditorData.stateContext: Jaheira weapons sheathed, player standing up

Text.Value: Your past is not my future.
Isobel was my doing... the rest of Last Light was an accident.
My rest was fine, until a looming druid came to pry.
I stole every little life in Last Light.
I don't owe you answers, especially not at sword-point.
Do not thank us, friend. It is not as if we didn't consider killing you instead.
But that would be a mercy. One you have not earned.
This is your father's true legacy. Not his children - but the fear they plant in us. The savagery it blossoms into.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Considering her blade

Text.Value: What? Evil cannot serve good, Jaheira. That is why it is evil.
What if I slip out of control again? You will kill me?
You are twice-tainted, yes. But whatever you have done - you might yet serve the good.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* DWS_CINE_Stow_01 for Jaheira stowing her weapons.<CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Relaxing, Jaheira sighs and shethes her weapons. She steps back [to stand beside Minsc if he's present], giving the player room to stand.

Text.Value: You first. I find that sleep escapes me, so I might as well take the watch.
So the game is up at last.
To watch over me - or to protect against me?
Sleep well.
Then we shall make this swift.
And what is it I owe? Should I allow some horror to be born anew, when I could end it here and now?
My birthright, in all its vile glory.
Kill me then, coward. I dare you to try.
I suppose you'll have your answer when you wake in the morning.
Leave the future for hathrans and hamsters to divine. We speak only of this moment.
If there is still good in you - find it quickly, says Boo. Or the next time we meet, you will know my rage.
STORIES!
My rest was fine, until a looming druid came to pry.
Whatever its source, the Slayer form is a weapon like any other. And if you mean to master it, I know where you must go.
That birthright may well bring you to a bloody end. How many should I allow to go with you?
As will I. Jaheira tells me a debt is owed - even if my heart and hamster do not understand it.
If I must lie awake, then so must you - only fair, considering that you are the reason.
As you wish, then. We take our leave. I hope you have mastered yourself, when next we meet. If not, we will do what we must.
The dreams alone do not concern me. It is what waking deeds they might inspire.
*The sleeping blood-beast within claws and scratches at your resting mind. You are, as ever, mere hairs away from its grasp.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Narration over black screen.

Text.Value: Then would you call it mercy, if the next night I never let you wake?
But not yours alone to walk.
I suppose you do not.
And so I come to ask: what did it take for you to earn that Slayer-skin you hide so well?
*The ranger's thoughts flit through your own, searching, probing for something specific. Until he finds...*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc and the player mind-melding

Text.Value: Thank you. For everything.
Helpless. Like I can deny him nothing.
The burden of your blood is yours to carry, but you need not carry it alone.
It might be that you have to turn and face her - you cannot change that. All you can choose is how you meet her: as another bloodied child of Bhaal, or as yourself.
Is this the reward for my confession? A dagger in the night?
Cast yourself into the dark if you wish. I mean to be there to pull you back - by the hand, or the scruff.
For now, take what rest you can - we will watch over you this night.
So - what did it take to earn that new Slayer-skin of yours?
And for this, you will need Boo. He has tasted Bhaalspawn flesh before - and he would not mind another bite.
How do I know you won't kill me?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: horror, denial

Text.Value: And if I embrace Father's power? Grant unto him my love?
I've been sensing something, you see. A formless but familiar dread, which I have only now been able to put a name to.
I believe it went over a cliff-edge, buried in an ogre's backside. And it was still talking...
Come on, let's go back to sleep.
Jaheira, he tried to make me... I almost...
Jaheira, she tried to make me... I almost...
Jaheira, they tried to make me... I almost...
For now, take what rest you can - I will watch over you this night.
How could you possibly know?
I have spent my life fighting your father in whatever form he chose to take. By rights, I should cut you down here.
Innocent blood. As innocent as my own: I have no control over when my body kills.
*Another watches your body, while it is possessed by the night. You do not dream alone.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot of player opening their eyes, and a figure standing over them about a pace away - Jaheira. The player sits up.

Text.Value: *A single prod is enough to send his fury into a twisted spiral, wrapping around you then storming over to Jaheira.*
You will answer for this, fiend. And it will be an answer of the screaming sort.
Poke at Minsc's mind to stoke his rage.
You would not be the first to turn the taint in your blood to your advantage. But there are barriers a Bhaalspawn must overcome, first.
I think you are still dreaming if you see a dagger before you. She has a sword - two of them, in fact.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc suddenly looms on the player's other side, surrounding them. He carries no weapon, but his hulking presence is threatening nonetheless.

Text.Value: I intend to become Bhaal's Chosen. So bow, or die.
Whatever path you choose, I fear it will lead you to the same point. The same enemy.
Are we so faithless? As you wish - while we watch over you, Boo shall be watching over us.
All I can offer is the promise that, should you choose to do so, you will not meet her alone.
Have you ever fought with a talking sword?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Butting in, blunt

Text.Value: You have not confessed it all, I think. There is something in the air tonight - the scent of a terrible and familiar power.
And when you stand against him, you will not stand alone.
Perhaps I was too swift to put up my blades. But we will not play into your father's hands this night.

EditorData.stateContext: Jaheira armed with two scimitars, Player seated

Text.Value: Or perhaps I will take you to my Father directly - as trophies.
Wait.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Holding hand up to Minsc, but never taking eyes off player.

Text.Value: My path is mine alone to choose.
Lilarcor.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera begins to pull out and voices fade as they continue talking into the night.

Text.Value: I won't sleep again. Tell me something of the old days, since they're on your mind.
'A better way?' It's too late. My cruel deeds cannot be undone.
Boo remembers the scent of Bhaalspawn. Like rot on the tongue - meaning no offence.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc suddenly looms on the player's other side, surrounding them. He carries no weapon, but his hulking presence is threatening nonetheless.

Text.Value: There we have our answer. But we might as well hear it from you.
How could you possibly know?
*For a moment, the briefest, weakest moment, Jaheira appears as she truly is. Simply an old woman, uncertain and afraid.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* Either CINE_Step_Back_StandR_01 or  CINE_StepBackwards_to_StandR_01, wichever fits best. <CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Taking a step back in shock

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* for Minsc: CINE_TurnLeft180_ToWalk_StandL_01, mirrored if necessary. For Jaheira: the same, but blend from CINE_StepBackwards_to_StandR_01
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Jaheira backs away and leaves, Minsc trailing behind.

Text.Value: For now, rest. Sleep escapes me, so I might as well take the watch.
We do not loom, friend. We tread soft and sure as hunting hamsters.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc suddenly looms on the player's other side, surrounding them. He carries no weapon, but his hulking presence is threatening nonetheless.

Text.Value: *A spike of rage, quickly muffled - Minsc's mind still lingers near your own, and he does not like what is coming to pass.*
But you have reminded us that when evil calls, we might stop our ears with virtuous cotton. Hasn't he, Jaheira?
But you have reminded us that when evil calls, we might stop our ears with virtuous cotton. Hasn't she, Jaheira?
But you have reminded us that when evil calls, we might stop our ears with virtuous cotton. Haven't they, Jaheira?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
Minsc walks to stand behind Jaheira.
IF DOABLE - he clasps her shoulder, as if reminding her.

Text.Value: Are you truly your own master? What is it you feel, when father's dreams come calling?
She is worrying. Which worries me. Which worries Boo. Which ought to worry you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc suddenly looms on the player's other side, surrounding them. He carries no weapon, but his hulking presence is threatening nonetheless.

Text.Value: Bathing in my dearest friend's gore.
My rest was fine, until a looming druid came to pry.
So the game is up at last.
You know better than that, Stone Lord. We found the good in you - and we found it in another Bhaalspawn, once before.
I've slept beside a Bhaalspawn before. I know the signs - the dreams, the urges... the power.
No need for such dramatics. I will go with eyes wide open - and the hope that I know you a little better than you know yourself.
Yes! A mighty blade, but a mouthy one, too. I wonder what happened to it.
Dark dreams?
Show daddy dear that you alone choose your fate. You are a child of Bhaal - but that need not be all that you are.
Almost. There is but one piece left to play.
I am truly bored of that phrase.
I don't - not yet.
How could you possibly know?
Tell me what I must do.
Ever the Bhaalspawn's lot. To bring death, or wait for it to find them.
Is this the reward for my confession? A dagger in the night?
Those of your kind. Orin - I am sure you already know that so long as she lives, she will never stop hunting you.
It's sickening. I never asked for this power, and hope to be rid of it.
So the game is up at last.
You will be protected. Even from yourself.

EditorData.stateContext: Jaheira weapons sheathed, player standing up

Text.Value: *Tonight's troubled rest is, as ever, overwhelmed by your killing fate. You dangle above a dark precipice, one move away from falling.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Narration over black screen.

Text.Value: What are you doing, Jaheira?
Don't patronise me. I can do without your guidance.
You are what you are, child of Bhaal. But that need not be all that you are.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Camera pulling out from camp, player falling to sleep with Jaheira / and Minsc sitting down beside them.

Text.Value: It would be like swinging a sword by the wrong side. Painful - but it can be effective, too.
*No more dreams await you in sleep this night. Only the warm knowledge that, indeed - you are not alone.*
And what will become of me, if I beat her?
To face the other of your kind - Orin. So long as the other lives, neither of you can claim your full power.
Bathing in my lover's gore.
There is one certain way. I hold it in my hand.
You have not confessed it all, I think.
What are you doing, Jaheira?
No game. A serious matter, to rouse Boo from his beauty sleep.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Minsc suddenly looms on the player's other side, surrounding them. He carries no weapon, but his hulking presence is threatening nonetheless.

Text.Value: What are you doing, Jaheira?

Synopsis: Jaheira and Minsc confront the Dark Urge about their recent revelation they are a Bhaalspawn. Depending on how much the player has given into Bhaal, they are either more sympathetic, or almost hostile. But either way, they are supportive and want to use their knowledge of fighting alongside Bhaalspawn in the past to convince you that you can do good
